<p>Key Education Resources</b> (KER), a subsidiary of KeyBank, is a nationwide education funding provider with over 50 years of experience providing Federal Education Loans, Private Education Loans, and Education Consolidation Loans.
<p>KER historically has used a number of outside services for credit scoring in its loan origination process. To meet the goal of minimizing the time and cost of loan origination, KER decided to try to make use of the credit scoring services of its parent company’s application processing system.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>KER engaged Nevo to meet the challenge of this integration goal&#8212;to seamlessly integrate KER’s Edison loan processing system with Key’s mainframe ACAPS system. Nevo designed and developed a stand-alone Java module based in the Edison database. The module consisted of a request agent that sent credit decision requests to the ACAPS mainframe via KeyServer, and a results agent that seamlessly inserted credit decisions back into Edison.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>Nevo’s solution sent and received messages using IBM’s MQSeries message queuing technology. Nevo collaborated and coordinated with both business and technology resources, over KER’s geographically dispersed organization.
